tures%20and%20stripped%20privacy%20protections%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Federal%20Trade%20Commission's%20antitrust%20buster%20said%20Americans%20lost%20a%20lot%20of%20privacy%20protection%20because%20a%20handful%20of%20large%20tech%20companies%20were%20allowed%20to%20go%20on%20an%20acquisition%20spree%20without%20greater%20scrutiny.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20%26quot%3B60%20Minutes%26quot%3B%20interview%20that%20aired%20Sunday%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fftc-chair-lina-khan-antitrust-critic-big-tech-amazon-2021-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFTC%20Chair%20Lina%20Khan%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20allowing%20Big%20Tech%20to%20go%20through%20hundreds%20of%20acquisitions%20in%20the%20past%20several%20decades%20was%20a%20mistake%20that%20hurt%20Americans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20technology%20markets%2C%20we%20went%20through%20a%20couple%20of%20decades%20where%20we%20saw%20over%20800%20acquisitions%20by%20the%20five%20big%20players%2C%20not%20a%20single%20one%20of%20which%20was%20blocked%2C%20and%20some%20of%20those%20we%20realized%20ended%20up%20leading%20to%20significant%20harm%2C%26quot%3B%20Khan%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20acknowledged%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-facebook-buying-whatsapp-2014-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFacebook's%20purchase%20of%20messaging%20app%20WhatsApp%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202014%20for%20%2419%20billion%20as%20one%20example.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-ftc-facebook-antitrust-lawsuit-is-important-2020-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFTC%20sued%20Facebook%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202020%2C%20accusing%20Mark%20Zuckerberg's%20company%20of%20engaging%20in%20anticompetitive%20practices%20by%20buying%20Instagram%20and%20WhatsApp.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EA%20district%20judge%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20dismissed%20the%20complaint%20in%20June%202021%2C%20stating%20that%20the%20agency%20did%20not%20provide%20enough%20evidence%20that%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Ffederal-court-dismisses-ftc-s-anti-trust-lawsuit-against-facebook-1030560379%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFacebook%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0established%20a%20monopoly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20case%20was%20revived%20after%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fruling-ftc-meta-facebook-lawsuit-instagram-whatsapp-can-proceed-2022-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFTC%20refiled%20the%20complaint%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20month%20later.%20In%20another%20motion%20to%20dismiss%20the%20lawsuit%20in%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EApril%2C%20Facebook%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2024-04-05%2Fmeta-asks-judge-to-throw-out-ftc-antitrust-case-before-trial%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enow%20Meta%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20it%20faces%20plenty%20of%20competition%20from%20rivals%20like%20TikTok%2C%20X%2C%20and%20YouTube.%20The%20company%20also%20said%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fabout.fb.com%2Fnews%2F2024%2F04%2Fmeta-files-motion-for-summary-judgment-in-ftc-lawsuit-relating-to-instagram-and-whatsapp%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epress%20statement%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20FTC%20reviewed%20the%20acquisition%20of%20Instagram%20and%20WhatsApp%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20decision%20to%20revisit%20done%20deals%20is%20tantamount%20to%20announcing%20that%20no%20sale%20will%20ever%20be%20final%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20company%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20FTC%20spokesperson%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%20A%20Meta%20spokesperson%20declined%20to%20provide%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKhan%20argued%20in%20the%20%26quot%3B60%20Minutes%26quot%3B%20interview%20that%20purchases%20like%20these%20weakened%20Americans'%20privacy%20guardrails.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BJust%20to%20give%20you%20a%20concrete%20example%2C%20there%20were%20companies%20that%20were%20offering%20Americans%20greater%20privacy%2C%20and%20they%20were%20promising%20that%20we're%20not%20going%20to%20use%20your%20data%2C%20we're%20not%20going%20to%20sell%20it%2C%20we're%20not%20going%20to%20spy%20on%20you%2C%20everywhere%20all%20the%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20Khan%20said.%20%26quot%3BAfter%20some%20of%20those%20firms%20were%20bought%20up%20by%20one%20of%20the%20big%20guys%2C%20all%20of%20those%20data%20privacy%20policies%20changed%20overnight%2C%20and%20so%20Americans%20lost%20those%20privacy%20protections.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhatsapp-forcing-users-to-share-personal-data-facebook-elon-musk-2021-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWhatsApp%20changed%20its%20privacy%20terms%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20force%20users%20to%20share%20their%20personal%20data%20with%20Facebook.%20Ireland's%20privacy%20watchdog%20fined%20the%20company%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhatsapp-fined-sharing-data-facebook-privacy-communication-users-mesaging-2021-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%24266%20million%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Efor%20issues%20related%20to%20transparency%20around%20how%20WhatsApp%20shared%20its%20data%20with%20Facebook.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20WhatsApp%20spokesperson%20told%20BI%20at%20the%20time%20that%20the%20company%20disagreed%20with%20the%20decision%20and%20that%20the%20penalties%20were%20%26quot%3Bentirely%20disproportionate.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20her%20appointment%20by%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20in%202021%2C%20Khan%20has%20led%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-lina-khan-wrong-about-hollywood-consolidation-market-structure-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaggressive%20antitrust%20fight%3C%2Fa%3E%20against%20large%20corporations%2C%20drawing%20the%20ire%20of%20Democratic%20and%20Republican%20business%20leaders.%20An%20FTC%20spokesperson