n%20the%20background.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5cf802b211e2051bc13c6f42%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222003%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EScammers%20who%20say%20they%20have%20your%20search%20history%20probably%20just%20bought%20your%20email%20from%20a%20data%20breach.%3Cp%3EOmar%20Marques%2FSOPA%20Images%2FLightRocket%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EPolice%20are%20warning%20about%20a%20growing%20number%20of%20email%20%26quot%3Bsextortion%26quot%3B%20scams.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EScammers%20will%20claim%20to%20have%20compromising%20search%20history%20and%20demand%20crypto%20to%20keep%20quiet.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBut%20they%20are%20almost%20certainly%20bluffing%2C%20authorities%20say.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20scary%20hacker%20in%20your%20email%20who%20says%20he%20recorded%20you%20visiting%20an%20adult%20website%20%E2%80%94%20and%20wants%20you%20to%20send%20him%20bitcoin%20to%20keep%20quiet%20about%20it%20%E2%80%94%20is%20most%20likely%20just%20a%20scammer%20who%20bought%20your%20email%20address%20after%20a%20data%20breach.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFederal%20and%20state%20police%20across%20the%20country%20warned%20about%20a%20rise%20in%20the%20number%20of%20email%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsextortion-targets-celebrities-sports-wealthy-ceos-lawyers-2022-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bsextortion%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20scams%20this%20month.%20The%20Maryland%20State%20Police%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20on%20Thursday%20that%20reports%20of%20one%20sextortion%20scam%20targeting%20Gmail%20users%20surged%20in%20August%20and%20September.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20these%20scams%2C%20someone%20tells%20a%20victim%20they%20have%20access%20to%20embarrassing%20search%20history%20or%20compromising%20photos.%20The%20scammers%20then%20demand%20money%20or%20they%20will%20release%20it%20to%20family%20and%20friends.%20They're%20almost%20always%20bluffing%2C%20police%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInducing%20fear%20and%20a%20time%20element%20are%20some%20of%20the%20most%20common%20tactics%20grifters%20use%20to%20get%20victims%20to%20quickly%20hand%20over%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fscammers-squeezed-330000-people-webcam-porn-2019-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elarge%20sums%20of%20money%3C%2Fa%3E%20before%20anyone%20realizes%20they've%20been%20duped.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BScammers%20want%20you%20to%20act%20before%20you%20have%20time%20to%20think%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20FTC%20says.%20%26quot%3BThey%20might%20say%20your%20computer%20is%20about%20to%20be%20corrupted.%20They%20also%20might%20tell%20you%20to%20keep%20the%20conversation%20a%20secret%20from%20your%20friends%20and%20family.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20types%20of%20email%20sextortion%20scams%20first%20surfaced%20in%202020%20when%20there%20was%20a%20spike%20in%20the%20number%20of%20people%20reporting%20that%20someone%20had%20hacked%20their%20computers%20and%20recorded%20them%20visiting%20adult%20websites%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fconsumer.ftc.gov%2Fconsumer-alerts%2F2020%2F04%2Fscam-emails-demand-bitcoin-threaten-blackmail%3Fpage%3D5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20FTC%20said%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20FTC%20says%20that%20these%20emails%20usually%20come%20to%20victims%20after%20their%20personal%20information%20is%20leaked%20in%20a%20data%20breach.%20This%20means%20the%20scammers%20may%20have%20access%20to%20your%20email%20and%20even%20some%20of%20your%20current%20or%20former%20passwords%2C%20but%20they%20do%20not%20have%20access%20to%20your%20computer%20or%20search%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20scammers%20may%20say%20they%20have%20access%20to%20your%20computer%20or%20webcam%2C%20or%20installed%20clever%20software%20to%20defeat%20you.%20That's%20all%20talk%2C%26quot%3B%20The%20FTC%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20scammers%20in%20Maryland%20even%20included%20images%20of%20the%20victim's%20house%20from%20Google%20Maps%20in%20their%20threats%20to%20make%20them%20seem%20legitimate%2C%20police%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Maryland%20State%20Police%20advise%20caution%20when%20receiving%20%26quot%3Bunsolicited%26quot%3B%20emails%20to%20your%20Gmail%20account%20to%20avoid%20becoming%20a%20victim%20of%20a%20scam.%20The%20department%20also%20advises%20against%20sharing%20personal%20information%20online.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20told%20Business%20Insider%20in%20a%20statement%20that%20it%20%26quot%3Btakes%20stopping%20threats%20like%20this%20seriously%26quot%3B%20and%20has%20%26quot%3Bextensive%20resources%20to%20help%20people%20identify%2C%20report%20and%20if%20necessary%2C%20recover%20from%20these%20types%20of%20scams.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20cases%20like%20this%20pop%20up%2C%20we%20work%20closely%20with%20law%20enforcement%20to%20stop%20malicious%20activity%20and%20protect%20users%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20company%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsextortion-scam-google-search-history-gmail-data-breach-2024-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1727027653000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66f01cfcce3009a0fac851a4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsextortion-scam-google-search-history-gmail-data-breach-2024-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Police%20say%20email%20sextortion%20scams%20are%20on%20the%20rise.%20Scammers%20will%20say%20they%20have%20compromising%20information.%20But%20they%20rarely%20do.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kniemeyer%40insider.com%20(Kenneth%20Niemeyer)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A37%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsextortion-scam-google-search-history-gmail-data-breach-2024-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Richa's%20unseen%20photos%