rmous-explosion-at-russian-ammunition-depot-ukraine-war-2024-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1727010658000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66f015e8d17aa3c7b2b4d4dd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvideo-enormous-explosion-at-russian-ammunition-depot-ukraine-war-2024-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Ukrainian%20military%20said%20that%202%2C000%20tons%20of%20munitions%2C%20including%20some%20from%20North%20Korea%2C%20had%20arrived%20at%20the%20depot%20before%20the%20strike.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22rrommen%40insider.com%20(Rebecca%20Rommen)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A103%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvideo-enormous-explosion-at-russian-ammunition-depot-ukraine-war-2024-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20rich%20Americans%20use%20life%20insurance%20to%20save%20on%20taxes%20and%20protect%20their%20kids'%20inheritance%20with%20this%20neat%20trick%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225370%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Stock%20image%20of%20rich%20family%20walking%20to%20their%20private%20jet%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66edc657d17aa3c7b2b4b36a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223580%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELife%20insurance%20can%20be%20used%20to%20save%20on%20taxes%20and%20protect%20inherited%20assets%20from%20creditors.%3Cp%3EJupiterimages%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EFor%20the%20wealthy%2C%20life%20insurance%20is%20an%20unsexy%20yet%20powerful%20tactic%20for%20avoiding%20taxes.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBy%20putting%20the%20policy%20inside%20a%20trust%2C%20the%20death%20benefit%20is%20excluded%20from%20estate%20taxes.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20payout%20goes%20to%20the%20trust%2C%20which%20pays%20Uncle%20Sam%20and%20protects%20the%20remaining%20assets%20from%20lawsuits.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EEstate%20taxes%20pose%20a%20dilemma%20for%20asset-rich%20but%20cash-poor%20Americans.%20To%20pay%20Uncle%20Sam%2C%20their%20heirs%20may%20be%20forced%20to%20liquidate%20their%20real%20estate%20empires%20or%20privately%20held%20businesses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20there%20is%20an%20alternative%20to%20a%20fire%20sale%3A%20They%20can%20use%20life%20insurance%20to%20foot%20the%20bill%20with%20a%20neat%20trick.%20Instead%20of%20owning%20a%20life%20insurance%20policy%20directly%2C%20they%20take%20out%20a%20policy%20and%20put%20it%20inside%20a%20trust.%20The%20irrevocable%20life%20insurance%20trust%20(ILIT)%20collects%20the%20death%20benefit%2C%20pays%20the%20tax%20bill%2C%20and%20distributes%20whatever%20is%20left%20according%20to%20the%20insured%20individual's%20wishes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAny%20payout%20is%20also%20protected%20from%20estate%20taxes%2C%20even%20if%20the%20insured's%20estate%20and%20death%20benefit%20exceed%20the%20exemption.%20(Currently%2C%20a%2040%25%20federal%20estate%20tax%20applies%20to%20estates%20exceeding%20%2413.61%20million).%20For%20an%20ultra-rich%20taxpayer%20with%20a%20%2410%20million%20life%20insurance%20policy%2C%20using%20an%20ILIT%20could%20save%20%244%20million%20in%20taxes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20low-hanging%20fruit.%20It%20succeeds%20in%20removing%20the%20insurance%20from%20the%20estate.%20It%20does%20not%20deprive%20anybody%20of%20access%20to%20anything%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Robert%20Strauss%2C%20partner%20at%20the%20law%20firm%20Weinstock%20Manion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20insured%20can%20select%20virtually%20anyone%20as%20the%20beneficiary%20such%20as%20business%20partners%20or%20friends.%20While%20it%20is%20less%20common%20now%2C%20ILITs%20have%20been%20%E2%80%94%20and%20can%20be%20%E2%80%94%20used%20to%20provide%20for%20unmarried%20partners%20or%20extramarital%20ones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHistorically%2C%20if%20an%20individual%20had%20a%20special%20friend%20that%20they%20wanted%20to%20benefit%2C%20life%20insurance%20inside%20the%20trust%20was%20one%20of%20the%20ways%20you%20could%20'take%20care%20of'%20that%20obligation%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Dan%20Griffith%2C%20the%20director%20of%20wealth%20strategy%20at%20Huntington%20Bank.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20other%20perks.%20As%20with%20other%20types%20of%20trusts%2C%20the%20insured%20can%20pick%20a%20trustee%20that%20manages%20how%20the%20funds%20are%20distributed%20to%20the%20beneficiaries.%20For%20instance%2C%20a%20grandchild%20can%20receive%20a%20distribution%20to%20pay%20for%20college%20tuition%20but%20not%20a%20sports%20car.%20The%20ILIT%20can%20also%20limit%20the%20future%20beneficiaries%2C%20excluding%20future%20partners%20of%20a%20surviving%20spouse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20insured%20wants%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20their%20heirs%20are%20protected%20from%20creditors%20or%20divorcing%20spouses%2C%20they%20can%20use%20ILITs%20to%20be%20doubly%20safe%2C%20Griffith%20added.%20Though%20law%20varies%20by%20state%2C%20trusts%20and%20life%20insurance%20both%20have%20strong%20legal%20protections.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEven%20if%2C%20for%20whatever%20reason%2C%20the%20creditor%20were%20able%20to%20get%20into%20the%20assets%20of%20the%20trust%2C%20the%20insurance%20policy%20could%20be%20protected%20by%20state%20law%20on%20its%20own%2C%26quot%3B%20Griffith%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22739dd19e-0c61-46bc-a56e-89f7debb7b2b%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHere's%20how%20ILITs%20work%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EILITs%20have%20to%20be%20properly%20structured%20to%20pass%20muster%20with%20the%20IRS.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ILIT%20must%20be%20named%20as%20the%20beneficiary%20of%20the%20life%20insurance%20policy.%20It%20must%20also%20own%20the%20policy.%20While%20you%20can%20transfer%20the%20policy%20to%20the%20ILIT%20as%20a%20gift%2C%20Strauss%20does%20not%20recommend%20this%20as%20the%20transfer%20is%20void%20if%20the%20insured%20dies%20within%20three%20years.%20Instead%2C%20he%20advises%20the%20grantor%20%E2%80%94%20the%20person%20who%20creates%20the%20trust%20%E2%80%94%20to%20provide%20cash%20or%20a%20loan%20to%20the%20ILIT%20so%20the%20trust%20can%20buy%20the%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20cash%20goes%20into%20the%20trust%2C%20there%20is%20a%20waiting%20period%20of%20typically%2030%20to%2060%20days%20during%20which%20beneficiaries%20can%20take%20money%20out.%20After%20the%20beneficiaries%20have%20been%20notified%20and%20the%20period%20elapses%2C%20the%20trust%20can%20use%20the%20cash%20to%20pay%20the%20premiums.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20these%20cash%20contributions%2C%20the%20grantor%20reduces%20the%20size%20of%20their%20taxable%20estate.%20They%20also%20do%20not%20incur%20gift%20tax%20if%20the%20grantor%20gifts%20%2418%2C000%20or%20less%20a%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20insured's%20death%2C%20the%20trust%20receives%20the%20death%20benefit.%20Whether%20to%20pay%20the%20estate%20tax%20should%20be%20left%20to%20the%20trustee's%20discretion%2C%20according%20to%20Griffith.%20If%20the%20trustee%20is%20obligated%20to%20pay%20the%20tax%20bill%2C%20the%20death%20benefit%20would%20be%20included%20in%20the%20taxable%20estate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20tax%20bill%20is%20paid%2C%20the%20remainder%20can%20be%20distributed%20in%20various%20ways.%20For%20instance%2C%20the%20ILIT%20can%20name%20the%20surviving%20spouse%20as%20the%20primary%20beneficiary%20and%20the%20children%20as%20secondary%20beneficiaries.%20The%20surviving%20spouse%20receives%20the%20assets%2C%20which%20pass%20on%20to%20the%20children%20free%20of%20estate%20tax%20after%20their%20passing%2C%20Strauss%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226e24e004-7bef-46b2-a031-276c87a17822%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThere%20are%20a%20few%20caveats%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Col%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ETrustees%20can%20get%20in%20trouble%20with%20the%20IRS%20by%20forgetting%20to%20notify%20beneficiaries.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Fol%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20devil%20is%20in%20the%20details.%20It%20is%20crucial%20to%20notify%20beneficiaries%20of%20their%20right%20to%20withdraw%20cash%20from%20the%20ILIT%20within%20a%20specified%20time%20period%20with%20what%20are%20known%20as%20Crummey%20notices%20-%20named%20after%20the%20taxpayer%20who%20coined%20the%20technique.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20practice%20dating%20back%20to%20the%201960s%2C%20it's%20surprisingly%20common%20for%20trustees%20to%20forget%20to%20notify%20beneficiaries.%20Strauss%20recalled%20one%20of%20his%20partner's%20clients%20trying%20to%20backdate%20his%20Crummey%20notices%2C%20printing%20them%20on%20a%20laser%20jet%20printer.%20The%20IRS%20detected%20that%20the%20notices%20had%20been%20generated%20after%20the%20fact%20as%20they%20predated%20the%20existence%20of%20laser%20jet%20printers.%20The%20ILIT%20was%20nullified%2C%20and%20the%20assets%20were%20included%20in%20the%20taxable%20estate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Col%20start%3D%5C%222%5C%22%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EMake%20sure%20you're%20getting%20a%20life%20insurance%20policy%20that%20makes%20financial%20sense.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Fol%3E%3Cp%3EStrauss%20advises%20clients%20to%20be%20cautious%20when%20dealing%20with%20commission-hungry%20life%20insurance%20payments%20and%20consider%20their%20future%20plans.%20For%20instance%2C%20a%20client%20with%20%24100%20million%20doesn't%20need%20%2440%20million%20of%20insurance%20to%20cover%20estate%20taxes%20if%20they%20plan%20to%20give%20away%20%2460%20million%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EILITs%20also%20work%20best%20with%20permanent%20life%20insurance%20policies%2C%20which%20are%20much%20more%20expensive%20than%20term%20policies.%20Multimillion-dollar%20permanent%20policies%20carry%20hefty%20premiums%2C%20which%20can%20be%20a%20drain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20clients%20who%20set%20up%20ILITs%20when%20they%20are%20young%20come%20to%20regret%20the%20decision%2C%20according%20to%20Kate%20Maier%2C%20vice%20president%20of%20investment%20advisory%20Wealth%20Enhancement%20Group.%20Tax%20policy%20changes%20over%20time%2C%20possibly%20negating%20the%20advantages%20of%20the%20ILIT.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOr%20in%20some%20cases%2C%20they%20need%20the%20money%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20they%20set%20it%20up%2C%20the%20future%20looked%20a%20lot%20brighter%20than%20it%20is%20now.%20It's%20difficult%20to%20get%20the%20money%20back%20out.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frich-life-insurance-estate-taxes-ilit-2024-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1727010422000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66edc866ce3009a0fac83228%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frich-life-insurance-estate-taxes-ilit-2024-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Life%20insurance%20can%20be%20used%20to%20pay%20Uncle%20Sam%20and%20save%20big%20on%20the%20tax%20bill.%20Here's%20how%20it%20works.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22hcuccinello%40businessinsider.com%20(Hayley%20Cuccinello)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A33%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frich-life-insurance-estate-taxes-ilit-2024-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Study%20In%20Japan%3A%20Explore%20Scholarships%20To%20Pursue%20Robotics%20Engineering%20Course%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EOsaka%20University%20has%20officially%20announced%20the%20registration%20schedule%20for%20the%202025%20intake%20of%20its%20MEXT-funded%20Master's%20and%20PhD%20programs%20in%20Robotics%20Engineering%20and%20Bioengineering%20at%20the%20Graduate%20School%20of%20Engineering%20Science.%20The%20application%20process%20will%20commence%20on%20November%201%2C%20and%20will%20close%20on%20November%2015%2C%202024.%20Successful%20applicants%20will%20begin%20their%20studies%20on%20October%201%2C%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20programmes%2C%20backed%20by%20the%20Japanese%20government%2C%20provide%20international%20students%20with%20an%20opportunity%20to%20access%20world-class%20education%20in%20cutting-edge%20fields.%20A%20total%20of%20four%20students%20will%20be%20admitted%20to%20each%20program%20across%20the%20three%20departments%3A%20the%20Department%20of%20Materials%20Engineering%20Science%2C%20the%20Department%20of%20Mechanical%20Science%20and%20Bioengineering%2C%20and%20the%20Department%20of%20Systems%20Innovation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EApplication%20Requirements%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETo%20be%20eligible%2C%20applicants%20must%20meet%20several%20criteria%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENationality%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Applicants%20must%20be%20from%20a%20country%20that%20maintains%20diplomatic%20relations%20with%20Japan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EVisa%20Requirement%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ENon-Japanese%20nationals%20are%20expected%20to%20obtain%20a%20resident%20(Student)%20visa%20upon%20enrollment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAge%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EApplicants%20should%20have%20been%20born%20on%20or%20after%20April%202%2C%201990.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEducational%20Background%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFor%20Master's%20programme%20applicants%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EA%20bachelor's%20degree%20from%20a%20Japanese%20university%20or%20expect%20to%20graduate%20before%20enrollment.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ESixteen%20years%20of%20formal%20education%20in%20another%20country%20or%20equivalent.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EBe%20recognised%20as%20academically%20equivalent%20to%20a%20university%20graduate%20by%20the%20Graduate%20School%20of%20Engineering%20Science.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFor%20Doctoral%20Program%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EHold%20a%20master's%20degree%20or%20expect%20to%20complete%20their%20master's%20program%20before%20enrollment.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EHave%20at%20least%20two%20years%20of%20research%20experience%20and%20be%20recognized%20for%20research%20capability%20equivalent%20to%20a%20master's%20degree.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELanguage%20Proficiency%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EApplicants%20must%20demonstrate%20English%20proficiency%20with%20scores%20above%2079%20for%20TOEFL-iBT%2C%20213%20for%20TOEFL-CBT%2C%20550%20for%20TOEFL-PBT%2C%20or%206.0%20for%20IELTS.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECultural%20Contribution%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20While%20studying%20in%20Japan%2C%20applicants%20are%20expected%20to%20engage%20in%20activities%20that%20foster%20mutual%20understanding%20between%20Japan%20and%20their%20home%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EScholarship%20Benefits%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuccessful%20candidates%20will%20receive%20substantial%20support%20throughout%20their%20studies.%20The%20scholarship%20will%20cover%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMonthly%20Allowance%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%C2%A5147%2C000%20for%20master's%20students.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%C2%A5148%2C000%20for%20doctoral%20students.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EExemptions%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Application%20fees%2C%20entrance%20examination%20fees%2C%20admission%20fees%2C%20and%20tuition%20at%20Osaka%20University%20will%20be%20waived.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20scholarship%20period%20will%20last%20for%20the%20duration%20necessary%20to%20complete%20the%20respective%20programs%2C%20with%20students%20repeating%20a%20year%20ineligible%20for%20continued%20funding.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.es.osaka-u.ac.jp%2Fen%2Fadmission-aid%2Fmext-granted%2Fimages%2FRobotics_2025.pdf%5C%22%3ECheck%20official%20notice%20here%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1727010180000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-09%2F3n67k08g_osaka-university_625x300_22_September_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Feducation%2Fstudy-in-japan-osaka-university-announces-registration-schedule-for-masters-and-phd-programmes-check-scholarship-other-de